{"name":"Appendix C - Magic Items","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Items","type":"text","_id":"xFMKYUhtcUJkSVzd","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p></p><p>@UUID[Item.wyYHOGW9NmChNXSr]{Cloak of Scales}</p><p>@UUID[Item.88WGeXlMcC36waKy]{Deep-eel Tongue}</p><p>@UUID[Item.9UrOoqa75MxebeyN]{Lantern of Thess}</p><p>@UUID[Item.p2QWLnS66byB4SJ1]{Stormspear of Thess}</p><p>@UUID[Item.SfRdaO3j8RpjquXu]{Wardstone}</p><p>@UUID[Item.4Fux45QTDbxytGzI]{The Moon Key}</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1665950702651,"modifiedTime":1665976468872,"lastModifiedBy":"cP1aqbcSMQN2jq1L"},"_id":"xvzY8H7t6yV0vjvo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cP1aqbcSMQN2jq1L":3}}
{"name":"Introduction","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Special Notes | Thank You","type":"text","_id":"D0UMM9xo8npwwDv9","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><strong>Thank You!</strong></h2><p>Thank you for purchasing <strong>Bloodlords of the Deep</strong>! This Adventure is a part of <strong>Mammoth Factory's</strong> monthly adventures we release for our Patreons and Tribes! You can find more content like this, including fully written adventure PDFs with Statblocks for all new creatures we create, STL Models for 3d Printing, and more over on our <a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/MammothFactory/posts\">Patreon</a> and on our <a href=\"https://www.myminifactory.com/users/MammothFactory\">Tribes</a>!</p><p></p><h2><strong>Maps &amp; Tokens</strong></h2><p>The maps for this Adventure are found in your Scenes Tab. They are set up with Token Vision and all Tokens for the creatures that you will encounter ready to go. Tokens can be found on the Actor Tab under Monsters and NPC's, depending on the circumstance.</p><p>There are seven interactive maps and two region maps Included in this adventure:</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Interactive</span></strong></span></p><ul><li><p>The Fairy Queen - 23 x 33</p></li><li><p>Freehouse - 33 x 23</p></li><li><p>The Wind's Widow - 33 x 23</p></li><li><p>Ancient Ruins Night - 25 x 35</p></li><li><p>Water Temple Night - 30 x 40</p></li><li><p>Waterfall - 24 x 36</p></li><li><p>Aboleth Temple - 23 x 33</p></li></ul><p><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Region</span></strong></span></p><ul><li><p>Island of Thess (Player version)</p></li><li><p>Island of Thess (GM version)</p></li></ul><p></p><h2><strong>Token Vision, Walls, Doors, Windows and Terrain</strong></h2><p>Line of sight is in use on all maps for Walls, Doors, Windows and Terrain on the included interactive maps. Make sure to set the PC tokens vision properties in their Prototype Token Settings tab on their character sheet. By default all PC tokens are set to Vision Disabled and Basic Vision mode.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Lighting Controls</strong></h2><p>All Light Sources are set up for you on the maps already using the Light Controls, but you can absolutely use them on other maps if you wish. You can copy and paste them to instantly create an ambient light with the same settings on any map.</p><p>Each Lighting Token can have two settings entered - Light Radius(ft) Dim, Bright. The tokens are all set up with an appropriate setting for their light as well as a color hex code that fits their palette.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"OGL","type":"text","_id":"xnHfeIbRDH1jwJGJ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:\"><strong>Notice of Open Game Content: This book contains Open Game Content, which may only be used in and under the terms of the Open Game License version 1.0a.<br style=\"box-sizing:content-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:\" />Open Game Content: The Open content featured in this book includes the statistics, monster names, abilities, traits, and spells also found in the 5e SRD.<br style=\"box-sizing:content-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:\" />Open Gaming License <br style=\"box-sizing:content-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:\" />The following text is the property of Wizards of the Coast, Inc. and is Copyright 2000 Wizards of the Coast, Inc (\"Wizards\"). All Rights Reserved. <br style=\"box-sizing:content-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:\" />1. Definitions: (a)\"Contributors\" means the copyright and/or trademark owners who have contributed Open Game Content; (b)\"Derivative Material\" means copyrighted material including derivative works and translations (including into oth